U.K. Continues Plan to Kill Serious Fraud Office, Times Reports

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-04-08T01:02:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/u-k-continues-plan-to-kill-serious-fraud-office-times-reports.html
The U.K. government is moving ahead
with plans to abolish the  Serious Fraud Office  and pass
responsibility for prosecuting large and complex frauds to the
 Crown Prosecution Service , the London-based Times reported,
citing a document the newspaper said it had seen.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
